text.content: How long does Seamoss last before spoiling?

title.plain_text: How long does Seamoss last before spoiling?

text.content:
Most Sea Moss gel has an average life span of about 2 to 3 weeks from when you receive your order and should be kept refrigerated.
You should always inspect all your food products before consumption.

text.content: How do I use Seamoss Gel?

title.plain_text: How do I use Seamoss Gel?

text.content:
Sea Moss is naturally rich in minerals, protein, and iodine. Adding 1 - 2 tablespoons of Sea Moss gel to your daily smoothies, drinks, or other foods,
over time, will help reduce mucus and inflammation throughout your body.

text.content: What does Sea Moss taste like?

title.plain_text: What does Sea Moss taste like?

text.content: Sea Moss itself does not have a taste. We wash our Sea Moss thoroughly and soak it with key lime when preparing our Sea Moss Gel, which helps to neutralize any of the ocean smell or taste.
